    "body": "### Problem\n\nI want to get the cursor position (line number) in terminal mode.\r\nThis is the part of the highlighted `TermCursorNC` .\r\n\r\nI checked following functions but could not find API that I want.\r\n\r\n```\r\n:h nvim_win_get_cursor \r\n:h getcurpos\r\n:h getline\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhat I want to achieve by this API is related to #8816 .\r\nI want to automatically enter insert mode only when the cursor position in the terminal buffer is visible.\r\nWhen the cursor position in the terminal is not in the window, I do not want it to enter INSERT mode because it is scrolling up.\r\n\r\nTo explain in concrete code, I want to define the following autocmd, which will only enter insert mode when the cursor is present in the current terminal window.\r\n\r\n```\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufEnter\", {\r\n  pattern = \"term://*\",\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    -- top line in window\r\n    local start_line = vim.fn.line(\"w0\")\r\n    -- bottom line in window\r\n    local end_line = vim.fn.line(\"w$\")\r\n    \r\n    -- could not get currently?\r\n    local cursor_line = XXX\r\n\r\n    if start_line <= cursor_line and cursor_line <= end_line then\r\n      vim.cmd.startinsert()\r\n    end\r\n  end,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nFor this I needed API of the title.\r\n\r\nIt would be good to have this API as it may be used for other purposes.\r\n\r\n",
